      "alt": "Here is the succinct alt text for **image_3.png**:\nA line graph titled \"Agentic Coding Performance by Effort Level,\" comparing four models: GLM-5.2, GLM-5.1, Claude Opus 4.8, and Claude Opus 4.7. The vertical axis measures coding score percentage (45% to 85%), and the horizontal axis measures average output tokens per task (10k to 90k). The lines track how model performance scales across effort levels labeled \"Low,\" \"Non-Thinking,\" \"High,\" or \"Max.\" Claude Opus 4.8 achieves the highest overall scores, plateauing around 78% at \"High\" and \"Max\" effort levels, while GLM-5.2 shows a steep performance increase from \"Non-Thinking\" to \"High\" effort, ultimately approaching 75% score at its \"Max\" setting.\n",
